<br>
1- Willsapper is easier to get than epic and is a much better taunt weapon.  You won't need to replace this until you are able to get an EB weapon.<br>
<br>
2- SoZ is cheaper to buy than a green scale, and 100hp's &amp; some AC make it a really nice off hand weapon.  When you aren't MA, you can change SoZ to main hand and still do decent damage.<br>
<br>
3- WS/SoZ combo is much better than epic.<br>
<br>
4- Doing epic requires Chardok killing.  You would be much better off avoiding trashing your Chardok faction so you can do the 85hp ring quest and the 100hp shoulder/arm/wrist quest.<br>
<br>
So...with the same amount of time/effort/money spent, you could have epics (which will shortly end up in a bag) or you could use WS/SoZ combo and have a 85hp ring/100hp shoulder/wrist/arm item.<br>
<br>
Take your pick.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ureinholt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reinholt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/02 4:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=542.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Green Scale, is this Good or Bad ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2- SoZ is cheaper to buy than a green scale, and 100hp's &amp; some AC make it a really nice off hand weapon. When you aren't MA, you can change SoZ to main hand and still do decent damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
